The paper focuses on object detection using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of attention mechanisms and contextual information also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and the evaluation on image datasets suggest a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of LSTM layers for generating attention maps suggests a potential fit for neural networks (cs.NE).
